Class StdDrawModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • jdraw.std.StdDrawModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DrawModel
    public class StdDrawModel
extends Object
implements DrawModel
    Provide a standard behavior for the drawing model. This class initially does not implement the methods in a proper way. It is part of the course assignments to do so.

      • getFigures

        public Stream<Figure> getFigures()
        Description copied from interface: DrawModel
        Returns a sequential Stream of figures with this draw model as its source. This stream can be used to iterate over all figures contained in this model. The order of the figures is the order in which the figures were added to the model (insertion-order). The order is interpreted by the view as "back-to-front".
        Specified by:
        getFigures in interface DrawModel
        Returns:
        a sequential Stream over the figures in this draw model

      • removeModelChangeListener

        public void removeModelChangeListener​(DrawModelListener listener)
        Description copied from interface: DrawModel
        Removes the specified model listener so that it no longer receives model events from this draw model. This method performs no function, nor does it throw an exception, if the listener specified by the argument was not previously added to this figure.
        Specified by:

      • setFigureIndex

        public void setFigureIndex​(Figure f,
                           int index)
        Description copied from interface: DrawModel
        Sets the index of a given figure. The order of the other figures in the model remains unchanged. If the figure is moved to a new place, then the model sends a DRAWING_CHANGED event to all registered model listeners.
        Specified by:
        setFigureIndex in interface DrawModel
        Parameters:
        f - the figure whose index has to be set
        index - the position at which the new figure should appear. The other figures are moved away.

      • removeAllFigures

        public void removeAllFigures()
        Description copied from interface: DrawModel
        Remove all figures from the draw model. This method is used when loading a drawing from a file in order to clear the old drawing before loading the new one.
        Specified by:
        removeAllFigures in interface DrawModel
